And now a page from our "Sondaggend" almanac: September 30, 1882, today 136 years ago, and WE TELTHER ... the day on which the future physicist Johannes Wilhelm "Hans" Geiger was born in Germany.
Geiger developed a method to detect and measure radioactivity, an invention that eventually led to the device called the Geiger counter.
